First, I need to identify the net profit - this is the amount of profit an entity retains after all expenses have been deducted from total revenue.

Looking at the income statement, I can see that "Net Profit" is listed directly with a value of 1290835.16 on 2024-02-05.

Now I need to identify 5 component sub-items that contribute to this net profit calculation:

1. Total Revenue: 16388736.33 (this is the starting point of the income statement)
2. Total Cost: 11600000.00 (this represents the cost of goods sold)
3. Total Expenses: 2702048.02 (this includes administrative, selling, depreciation, and financial expenses)
4. Interest Income: 23583.67 (this is added to profit)
5. Tax Expense: 819436.82 (this is subtracted to get the final net profit)

The calculation checks out:
Total Revenue (16388736.33) - Total Cost (11600000.00) - Total Expenses (2702048.02) + Interest Income (23583.67) - Tax Expense (819436.82) = Net Profit (1290835.16)
